.nh
.TH schedctl-info 1

.SH NAME
schedctl-info \- show metadata for a scheduler image


.SH SYNOPSIS
schedctl-info

.EX
[--driver|-d]=[value]
[--output|-o]=[value]
[--version]=[value]
.EE


.SH DESCRIPTION
Show metadata embedded in a scheduler image: title, description,
documentation link, source repository, minimum kernel version, and the
other standard OCI annotations the image exposes.

.PP
SCHEDULER is either a name from schedctl list or a fully-qualified
container image reference. The image is queried from the registry; no
container runtime is required.

.PP
Examples:
  schedctl info scx_rusty
  schedctl info scx_rusty --version v1.0.0
  schedctl info ghcr.io/myorg/custom-scheduler -o json

.PP
\fBUsage\fP:

.EX
schedctl info SCHEDULER
.EE


.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
\fB--driver, -d\fP="": container runtime to use: containerd, podman (default: "podman")

.PP
\fB--output, -o\fP="": output format: text, json (default: "text")

.PP
\fB--version\fP="": image tag to inspect, e.g. v1.0.0
